The static design should have an abstract and two paragraphs for each article card. This information is
necessarily included in the HTML of the /blob/index.html document.
The dynamic blog index can make use of this by hiding the first two paragraphs and displaying only the
abstract. After the first two paragraphs have been revealed (paragraphs>=2) the requests for more
paragraphs can be sent to the web server onEllipsisButtonClick.

If the user's desire is to read from their last position then that paragraph or section is scrolled into view.
